# wn-inventory-app environment template.
#
# Copy to `.env` and adjust. PLACEHOLDERS ONLY — never commit real secrets.
# All NUXT_PUBLIC_* keys are non-secret (they ship to the browser) and override
# the dev defaults declared in nuxt.config.ts runtimeConfig.public.

# --- Backend wiring (dev) ----------------------------------------------------
# The app addresses the backend with SAME-ORIGIN relative paths
# (/_user/api, /_journal/api, /api/realtime), so there is no cross-origin
# request and no CORS — in dev OR prod. In dev those paths are proxied to
# NUXT_DEV_BACKEND_ORIGIN; in prod the app is served same-origin with the backend.
# This ALSO becomes the SSR internalApiOrigin in dev (see nuxt.config.ts), so a
# hard reload validates your local auth_token against THIS backend — not prod.
# Point this at your running WinterCMS backend:
NUXT_DEV_BACKEND_ORIGIN=http://localhost:8000

# Override the public API bases ONLY if the backend lives on a genuinely
# different origin than the app — in which case that backend MUST send CORS
# headers for the app origin (config/cors.php `paths`). Leave these unset for the
# same-origin / dev-proxy default.
# NUXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE=
# NUXT_PUBLIC_USER_API_BASE=
# NUXT_PUBLIC_JOURNAL_API_BASE=

# --- Realtime (Centrifugo) ---------------------------------------------------
# WS endpoint the browser connects to. Leave EMPTY to gracefully disable realtime
# (the app boots fine; the Realtime panel just shows "disconnected").
# This is a DIRECT cross-origin socket (NOT proxied). To enable realtime:
#   1. Set this to your Centrifugo connection endpoint, e.g.
#        ws://localhost:8787/connection/websocket
#   2. Add the app origin (e.g. http://localhost:3118) to Centrifugo's
#        client.allowed_origins  (else the WS handshake is rejected, silently).
#   3. On the BACKEND set, to match your Centrifugo config:
#        CENTRIFUGO_SECRET  = Centrifugo client.token.hmac_secret_key
#        CENTRIFUGO_API_KEY = Centrifugo http_api.key
#        CENTRIFUGO_API_URL = http://<centrifugo-host>:<port>/api
#      The backend mints a per-user connection JWT at GET /api/realtime/token
#      (jwt.auth-gated — the user must be logged in). See the Golem15.WebSockets
#      plugin for the backend side.
NUXT_PUBLIC_CENTRIFUGO_WS_URL=

# --- SEO ---------------------------------------------------------------------
# Public site URL (used by @nuxtjs/seo for canonical/sitemap/OG).
NUXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL=http://localhost:3118

# --- Playwright E2E (demo credentials only — NOT real secrets) ---------------
# A seeded backend test user for the login/auth smoke specs.
E2E_EMAIL=demo@example.com
E2E_PASSWORD=changeme
# Frontend URL the E2E suite targets.
E2E_FRONTEND_URL=http://localhost:3118
